# Frontend Web UI Architecture

## Structure
- Use feature-based organization.
- Keep routes/pages thin; they should only compose UI and call feature logic.
- Shared UI components live in `components/`.
- Feature logic lives in `features/<feature>/`.

## Components
- Single responsibility per component.
- Small, reusable, composable.
- Shared UI patterns go to common components.

## Business Logic
- Do not place business logic inside pages/routes.
- Business logic must live in services, hooks, or feature modules.
- API calls must be isolated in services.

## State
- Local UI state stays in components.
- Cross-feature state uses a store or context.

## Performance
- Avoid heavy computations inside render.
- Lazy-load large components where possible.

## Dependency & Deprecated Safety
- Do not use deprecated components or APIs.
- Prefer actively maintained libraries.
- Update code if deprecated APIs exist.
